  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      entGlycemic control has been found to improve clinical outcomes following Coronary Bypass
      Surgery. This study tests the hypothesis that obtaining tighter glycemic control(80-120mg/dl)
      as opposed to more moderate control (120-180mg/dl) will further improve outcomes.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      150 diabetic patients will be randomized to achieve aggressive glycemic control (80-120mg/dl)
      vs moderate control (120-180mg/dl) using intravenous insulin infusions beginning at
      anesthetic induction and continuing for 18 hours following surgery.
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
